      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 27 Aug. 1884 ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.08.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">B84/7546, unit 51, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27 Aug. 1884</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your letter of yesterday,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>T. Wilson to M, 26 August 1884.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>conveying the Chief Secretary's approval of Mr Gerhard Renner's appointment of junior Assistant in the Gov. Botanists Department vice Léon Henry resigned.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Regarding Henry's resignation and replacement see<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>L. Henry to M,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>18<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>July 1884<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 84-07-18c); M to T. Wilson,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>25<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>July 1884;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to T. Wilson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>28 July<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1884; M to T. Wilson,15 August 1884<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 84-08-15a); and M to G. Berry, 20 August 1884,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray express to the hon. Graham Berry my best thanks for having sanctioned this proposition, and kindly inform the hon. Gentleman, that the kindness, thus shown by the Chief Secretary will be brought on my request by Mr Renner with Mr Berry's name at once under the notice of her Imperial Highness, the Crown princess of Germany,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Princess Victoria Adelaide, eldest daughter of Queen Victoria and wife of Crown Prince Friedrich of Prussia.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>who caused on her private expense this orphan to be educated during a period of six years. I have no direct communication from H. Imp. Highness; but letters carried by Mr. Renner from his uncle and granduncle in Germany, both divines, bear out the patronage thus shown in a most generous and condescending manner by the Princess Royal of England to young Renner. If I was wrong, in not mentioning this at once in my submitting his name, then I can only say, that I really did not know how to act because I feared, that it might appear, that I had merely recommended his appointment on account of high patronage, not in consequence of merit.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obed.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Renner will enter on his duties to morrow, 28. Aug. 1884.</p>
         </div>
